hwVoGeneralJitterLen.name: hwVoGeneralJitterLen
hwVoGeneralJitterLen.description: This object specifies the length of the Jitter buffer. The default value is 3.

hwVoGeneralMatchPolicy.name: hwVoGeneralMatchPolicy
hwVoGeneralMatchPolicy.description: This object specifies match number policy of this gateway. The default value is short.

hwVoGeneralSendPerformance.name: hwVoGeneralSendPerformance
hwVoGeneralSendPerformance.description: This object specifies the performance of sending voice data. The default value is normal.

hwVoGeneralReceivePerformance.name: hwVoGeneralReceivePerformance
hwVoGeneralReceivePerformance.description: This object specifies the performance of receiving voice data. The default value is normal

hwVoGeneralCallStart.name: hwVoGeneralCallStart
hwVoGeneralCallStart.description: Set the start mode of called over IP

hwVoGeneralSpecialServiceEnable.name: hwVoGeneralSpecialServiceEnable
hwVoGeneralSpecialServiceEnable.description: This object sepcifies whether special service number function is enable or disable.

hwVoGeneralCallTransferSpecialServiceNum.name: hwVoGeneralCallTransferSpecialServiceNumber
hwVoGeneralCallTransferSpecialServiceNum.description: This object specifies the call-transfer special service number in talking.

hwVoGeneralPeerSearchStop.name: hwVoGeneralPeerSearchStop
hwVoGeneralPeerSearchStop.description: This object specifies the maximum in searching entities.

hwVoGeneralPeerSelectOrderRule.name: hwVoGeneralPeerSelectOrderRule
hwVoGeneralPeerSelectOrderRule.description: This object specifies the rule order applied in voice entity selection. 0 --- explicit match, priority, random 1 --- explicit match, priority, longest no use 2 --- explicit match, longest no use, priority 3 --- explicit match, longest no use, random 4 --- priority, explicit match, random 5 --- priority, explicit match, longest no usep 6 --- riority, longest no use, explicit match 7 --- priority, longest no use, random 8 --- longest no use, explicit match, priority 9 --- longest no use, explicit match, random 10 --- longest no use, priority, explicit match 11 --- longest no use, priority, random 12 --- explicit match, random 13 --- priority, random 14 --- longest no use, random 15 --- explicit match 16 --- priority 17 --- random 18 --- longest no use

hwVoGeneralPeerSelectTypePriority.name: hwVoGeneralPeerSelectTypePriority
hwVoGeneralPeerSelectTypePriority.description: This object specifies the priority-ranked type of voice entity. 1ST 2DN 3RD 0 --- NONE TYPE 1 --- VOIP POTS VOFR 2 --- VOIP VOFR POTS 3 --- POTS VOIP VOFR 4 --- POTS VOFR VOIP 5 --- VOFR POTS VOIP 6 --- VOFR POTS POTS

hwVoDialExpansionTable.name: hwVoDialExpansionTable
hwVoDialExpansionTable.description: The table contains the information of the Dial Expansion Record .

hwVoDialExpansionEntry.name: hwVoDialExpansionEntry
hwVoDialExpansionEntry.description: The information regarding a Dial Expansion Record.

hwVoDialExpansionType.name: hwVoDialExpansionType
hwVoDialExpansionType.description: The call direction of the Dial Expansion.

hwVoDialExpansionSource.name: hwVoDialExpansionSource
hwVoDialExpansionSource.description: This source telephone of the Dial Expansion.

hwVoDialExpansionTarget.name: hwVoDialExpansionTarget
hwVoDialExpansionTarget.description: This target telephone of the Dial Expansion.

hwVoDialExpansionRowStatus.name: hwVoDialExpansionRowStatus
hwVoDialExpansionRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

hwVoLtoPTable.name: hwVoLtoPTable
hwVoLtoPTable.description: The table contains the relation information of Voice logic channel and voice physical channel.

hwVoLtoPEntry.name: hwVoLtoPEntry
hwVoLtoPEntry.description: The information regarding a single logic voice channel .

hwVoLtoPChannel.name: hwVoLtoPChannel
hwVoLtoPChannel.description: The number of this logic voice channel .

hwVoLtoPSlot.name: hwVoLtoPSlot
hwVoLtoPSlot.description: The physical slot number which this logic voice channel based on.

hwVoLtoPPort.name: hwVoLtoPPort
hwVoLtoPPort.description: The physical port number which this logic voice channel based on.

hwVoLtoPTimeSlot.name: hwVoLtoPTimeSlot
hwVoLtoPTimeSlot.description: The timeslots map this logic channel is using . -1 represent this channel cann't be used by voice.

hwVoLtoPStatus.name: hwVoLtoPStatus
hwVoLtoPStatus.description: The current status of the physical voice channel.

hwVoLtoPBoardType.name: hwVoLtoPBoardType
hwVoLtoPBoardType.description: The board type of the physical voice channel.

hwVoLtoPPortNumber.name: hwVoLtoPPortNumber
hwVoLtoPPortNumber.description: The global port number of the logic voice channel. -1 represent this channel cann't be used by voice.

hwVoLtoPGroupNumber.name: hwVoLtoPGroupNumber
hwVoLtoPGroupNumber.description: The global group number of the logic voice channel. . -1 represent this channel cann't be used by voice .

hwVoNumSubstTable.name: hwVoNumSubstTable
hwVoNumSubstTable.description: The table is the number-substitute rule table. It contains the table index, dot match rule and the first rule tag that the rule is used firstly.

hwVoNumSubstEntry.name: hwVoNumSubstEntry
hwVoNumSubstEntry.description: A number-substitute rule list. One entry per number-substite rule list.

hwVoNumSubstIndex.name: hwVoNumSubstIndex
hwVoNumSubstIndex.description: The index uniquely identifies a number-substitute rule list. It is valid if its value is between 1 and 2147483647.

hwVoNumSubstFirstRule.name: hwVoNumSubstFirstRule
hwVoNumSubstFirstRule.description: This object specifies the first rule to be used firstly. It is valid if its value is between 0 and 127.

hwVoNumSubstDotMatchRule.name: hwVoNumSubstDotMatchRule
hwVoNumSubstDotMatchRule.description: This object specifies the dot wildcard match rule. end-only - only end of E.164 number (input format) left-right - match form left to right (input format) right-left - match form right to left (input format)

hwVoNumSubstRowStatus.name: hwVoNumSubstRowStatus
hwVoNumSubstRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

hwVoNumSubstRuleTable.name: hwVoNumSubstRuleTable
hwVoNumSubstRuleTable.description: The table contains the number-substitute rule information that is used to create an rule row with an appropriate rule index.

hwVoNumSubstRuleEntry.name: hwVoNumSubstRuleEntry
hwVoNumSubstRuleEntry.description: A single number-substitute rule. One entry per number-substitute rule.

hwVoNumSubstRuleIndex.name: hwVoNumSubstRuleIndex
hwVoNumSubstRuleIndex.description: The index uniquely identifies a number-substitute rule. It is valid if its value is between 0 and 127.

hwVoNumSubstRuleInputFormat.name: hwVoNumSubstRuleInputFormat
hwVoNumSubstRuleInputFormat.description: This object specifies the input match format that must be of the form ^(\^)!(\+)!([0-9ABCD.*%!#]+)(\$)!$.

hwVoNumSubstRuleOutputFormat.name: hwVoNumSubstRuleOutputFormat
hwVoNumSubstRuleOutputFormat.description: This object specifies the output format that must be of the form ^[0-9#.]+$.

hwVoNumSubstRuleRowStatus.name: hwVoNumSubstRuleRowStatus
hwVoNumSubstRuleRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

hwVoMaxCallTableIndex.name: hwVoMaxCallTableIndex
hwVoMaxCallTableIndex.description: The index uniquely identifies a single maximum call value. It is valid if its value is between 1 and 2147483647.

hwVoMaxCallValue.name: hwVoMaxCallValue
hwVoMaxCallValue.description: This object specifies a single maximum call value. It is valid if its value is between 0 and 120.
